page.title: 04CREDITS
page.content: The area has been surveyed and written about by members of the Combe Martin Historical Society with the help of friends and neighbours. Photographs have been supplied by the Warden of the Exmoor National Park. It is regretted that the information supplied is not more comprehensive but a 31 January 1986 deadline left the Society only ten days to collect information on this block and the one to the south of it. The information was stored on disk by a member of the Society. The photographs are the only ones available to us and the deadline left no time to get others taken and processed.
